neurotic quests.

00:03:00.830 --> 00:03:03.160
Consider Bacon's metaphors

00:03:03.160 --> 00:03:06.600
which expressly identify
the early scientists

00:03:06.600 --> 00:03:09.320
as a masculine seducer.

00:03:09.320 --> 00:03:11.840
The naturalists,
according to Bacon,

00:03:11.840 --> 00:03:15.330
wants to penetrate the
inner, into the inner

00:03:15.330 --> 00:03:19.390
and further recesses of nature
and to find a way, at length,

00:03:19.390 --> 00:03:21.300
into her inner chambers.

00:03:21.300 --> 00:03:25.820
If the natural philosopher
seduces, then, nature submits.

00:03:25.820 --> 00:03:28.530
It is no wonder if nature
will not give herself

00:03:28.530 --> 00:03:30.410
into their hands.

00:03:30.410 --> 00:03:33.790
When Bacon's writings
represent nature as female,

00:03:33.790 --> 00:03:37.120
the imagine that scientific
scrutiny is both a form

00:03:37.120 --> 00:03:40.970
of sexual analysis and
an occasion for conquest

00:03:40.970 --> 00:03:44.930
and containment by the
