00:04:18.030 --> 00:04:21.200
My topic today concerns
seduction plots

00:04:21.200 --> 00:04:24.830
and texts devoted to
teaching scientific ideas.

00:04:24.830 --> 00:04:28.340
For they picture characters
undergoing an intellectual

00:04:28.340 --> 00:04:30.850
conversion to its principles.

00:04:30.850 --> 00:04:33.860
And, my focus is on two
dialogues translated

00:04:33.860 --> 00:04:36.520
into English from
French and Italian.

00:04:36.520 --> 00:04:40.060
Fontenelle's study of Copernican
and Cartesian cosmology

00:04:40.060 --> 00:04:45.340
from 1686 and Francesco
Algarotti's rendering

00:04:45.340 --> 00:04:48.640
of Newtonian optics in 1737.

00:04:48.640 --> 00:04:51.930
So first Fontenelle.

00:04:53.420 --> 00:04:57.030
Bernard Le Bovier de
Fontenelle was a major figure

00:04:57.030 --> 00:04:59.070
of the French Enlightenment
for the duration

00:04:59.070 --> 00:05:03.490
of his long nearly
100 years of his life.

00:05:03.490 --> 00:05:07.620
In 1686, he published
his most famous work,

00:05:07.620 --> 00:05:11.740
Entretiens sur la pluralite
des mondes, an explication

00:05:11.740 --> 00:05:14.490
of Copernican and
Cartesian cosmology.

00:05:14.490 --> 00:05:17.500
It was, in France, an
instant best seller resulting

00:05:17.500 --> 00:05:20.850
in 4 editions in 3 years
and 33 more editions

00:05:20.850 --> 00:05:23.170
up to the author's
death in 1757.

00:05:23.170 --> 00:05:28.630
And, a sign of his influence and
his radicalism, it was placed

00:05:28.630 --> 00:05:31.800
on the Papel Index
[assumed spelling] in 1687.

00:05:31.800 --> 00:05:35.550
and Fontenelle was elected
to the french Academy

00:05:35.550 --> 00:05:38.430
in shortly thereafter.

00:05:38.430 --> 00:05:41.350
In 1697, he began
his appointment

00:05:41.350 --> 00:05:46.420
as Perpetual Secretary of
the Academy of Sciences

00:05:46.420 --> 00:05:48.790
which he held unto 1740.

00:05:48.790 --> 00:05:53.760
He was, in short, a gatekeeper
of French science studies.

00:05:53.760 --> 00:05:58.730
Now, Fontenelle uses dialogue
to challenge Heliocentrism.

00:05:58.730 --> 00:06:01.280
This is the belief
held by the character

00:06:01.280 --> 00:06:02.580
of the Martianess
[assumed spelling]

00:06:02.580 --> 00:06:05.060
when she first meets
the philosopher,

00:06:05.060 --> 00:06:07.630
her interlocutor
in the dialogue.

00:06:07.630 --> 00:06:11.190
Fontenelle's lady is of a
superior rank to her tutor.

00:06:11.190 --> 00:06:14.220
And, Algarotti follows
this example.

00:06:14.220 --> 00:06:16.790
Throughout the pages
of the discovery,

00:06:16.790 --> 00:06:18.800
the philosopher teaches
the Martianess

00:06:18.800 --> 00:06:22.200
about Copernican cosmology
and Cartesian physics,

00:06:22.200 --> 00:06:25.160
specifically the theory of
Fortesis [assumed spelling].

00:06:25.160 --> 00:06:29.400
In the Cartesian understanding,
particles are always in motion

00:06:29.400 --> 00:06:32.230
and always in contact with
each other each spinning

00:06:32.230 --> 00:06:33.970
like a planet.

00:06:33.970 --> 00:06:37.710
Decartes' Vortices were
disproved by Newton's theory

00:06:37.710 --> 00:06:39.230
of gravity the year

00:06:39.230 --> 00:06:41.980
after Fontenelle
published the Discovery.

00:06:41.980 --> 00:06:44.930
But, Cartesian physics remained
intellectually plausible

00:06:44.930 --> 00:06:46.500
for the next 50 years.

00:06:46.500 --> 00:06:47.800
And, this is something
that I always want

00:06:47.800 --> 00:06:49.370
to underscore with may students.

00:06:49.370 --> 00:06:53.100
Even though a theory may have
been disproven immediately,

00:06:53.100 --> 00:06:56.530
the original theory continues
to linger and seem plausible.

00:06:56.530 --> 00:06:59.450
You don't have historical
change overnight.

00:06:59.450 --> 00:07:04.890
And, Fontenelle, himself,
expresses admiration for Newton

00:07:04.890 --> 00:07:07.540
but he was not convinced by him.

00:07:07.540 --> 00:07:11.430
Now, the genre that
Fontenelle chooses is important.

00:07:11.430 --> 00:07:15.200
It's a dialogue between a
philosopher and a noble woman

00:07:15.200 --> 00:07:18.050
which allows for, in
Fontenelle's words,

00:07:18.050 --> 00:07:21.430
liberty of natural conversation.

00:07:21.430 --> 00:07:26.070
The dialogue's dialectic quality
enacts the process of learning.

00:07:26.070 --> 00:07:30.300
Making mistakes and having them
corrected is part of learning.

00:07:30.300 --> 00:07:33.430
It's not an occasion
to abandon the inquiry.

00:07:33.430 --> 00:07:36.060
The French Salon culture,

00:07:36.060 --> 00:07:39.090
in which powerful women
were active leaders,

00:07:39.090 --> 00:07:43.560
was especially amendable to
these sorts of conversations.

00:07:43.560 --> 00:07:46.680
Fontenelle's was a world
organized by elaborate rules

00:07:46.680 --> 00:07:50.650
of social etiquette, practices
that reflected the ideals

00:07:50.650 --> 00:07:54.070
of lightness, gallantry
and gallantry.

00:07:54.070 --> 00:07:57.250
These social norms shaped some
of the earliest reputations

00:07:57.250 --> 00:07:59.950
of enlighten philosophers.

00:07:59.950 --> 00:08:01.280
All of this gets incorporated

00:08:01.280 --> 00:08:03.670
into how Fontenelle
imagines the conversation

00:08:03.670 --> 00:08:06.560
between the noble
woman and her tutor.

00:08:06.560 --> 00:08:10.950
Within the dialogue, Fontenelle
eludes to the genre of romance,

00:08:10.950 --> 00:08:12.660
a reference that has the effect

00:08:12.660 --> 00:08:15.100
of easing the dialogue's
conjunction

00:08:15.100 --> 00:08:16.400
of science and seduction.

00:08:16.400 --> 00:08:18.940
In his preference, he explains,

00:08:18.940 --> 00:08:21.290
I'm going to give
you a long quotation.

00:08:21.290 --> 00:08:26.690
He writes, it is not to
penetrate by force of mediation

00:08:26.690 --> 00:08:31.200
into a thing that's obscure
in itself or anything

00:08:31.200 --> 00:08:36.320
that is obscurely explained, tis
only to read and to represent

00:08:36.320 --> 00:08:41.650
to yourselves at the same what
you read and to form some image

00:08:41.650 --> 00:08:45.900
of it that may be clear and free
from perplexing difficulties.

00:08:45.900 --> 00:08:49.970
I ask of the ladies, for this
system, that the same attention

00:08:49.970 --> 00:08:53.130
that they must give
the Princess of Cleves,

00:08:53.130 --> 00:08:55.600
if they would follow
the intrigue and find

00:08:55.600 --> 00:08:57.070
out the beauties of it.

00:08:57.070 --> 00:09:00.590
Though, the truth is that the
ideas of this book are not

00:09:00.590 --> 00:09:03.520
so familiar to the most
part of ladies as those

00:09:03.520 --> 00:09:05.580
of the Princess of Cleves.

00:09:05.580 --> 00:09:08.670
But, they are not more obscure
than those of that novel,

00:09:08.670 --> 00:09:11.500
and yet, they need not
think above twice at most.

00:09:11.500 --> 00:09:14.750
And, they will be capable
of taking a true measure

00:09:14.750 --> 00:09:17.840
and having a just
sense of the whole.

00:09:17.840 --> 00:09:22.170
Now, to set back for a
moment, Fontenelle's point is

00:09:22.170 --> 00:09:25.960
that reading about Natural
philosophy, beginners reading

00:09:25.960 --> 00:09:29.260
about natural philosophy is
just as foreign as reading

00:09:29.260 --> 00:09:33.380
about love affair in the
16th century French court.

00:09:33.380 --> 00:09:36.990
With this illusion to
Madame de Lafayette's novel,

00:09:36.990 --> 00:09:40.810
Fontenelle enjoys his readers
to interpret the discovery

00:09:40.810 --> 00:09:44.880
as though they were attending to
the detailed nuances and turns

00:09:44.880 --> 00:09:47.210
of seduction narrative.

00:09:47.210 --> 00:09:49.440
Such reading is an
active engagement

00:09:49.440 --> 00:09:52.170
in the process of
representation.

00:09:52.170 --> 00:09:54.090
Near the conclusion
of the discovery,

00:09:54.090 --> 00:09:56.380
the Martianess reflects
upon the effect

00:09:56.380 --> 00:10:00.810
of the scientific education
on her sense of self.

00:10:00.810 --> 00:10:03.840
She says I find the
worlds, the heavens,

00:10:03.840 --> 00:10:07.310
and the celestial bodies,
so subject to change

00:10:07.310 --> 00:10:11.200
that I am altogether
returned to myself.

00:10:11.200 --> 00:10:14.510
This return to myself is
not an attempt to reject

00:10:14.510 --> 00:10:18.690
or renounce the self-subjective
bias, but, to welcome it.

00:10:18.690 --> 00:10:22.210
Learning requires the
ability, in Fontenelle's words,

00:10:22.210 --> 00:10:26.370
to represent to yourselves
at the same what you read,

00:10:26.370 --> 00:10:30.330
to form some image of it
and maybe clear and free.

00:10:30.330 --> 00:10:32.800
In the Lochian Lexicon
[assumed spelling],

00:10:32.800 --> 00:10:35.660
this is the imagination
which fiction writers

00:10:35.660 --> 00:10:38.910
in the 18th century
understood as enabling learning

00:10:38.910 --> 00:10:41.400
through fiction and feeling.

00:10:41.400 --> 00:10:46.250
Fontenelle insists that a
good reader is a good learner.

00:10:46.250 --> 00:10:49.820
And, this individual actively
engages the imagination

00:10:49.820 --> 00:10:54.240
to apprehend new ideas,
concepts, and materials.

00:10:54.240 --> 00:10:57.350
Anyone conversant in
the language of romance,

00:10:57.350 --> 00:11:00.870
such as La Princess de
Cleves, is equally capable

00:11:00.870 --> 00:11:04.170
of using her attention
and imagination

00:11:04.170 --> 00:11:07.830
to understand Copernicus
and Decartes.

00:11:07.830 --> 00:11:11.260
Now, the genre of romance
has long been associated

00:11:11.260 --> 00:11:12.970
with absorptive reading,

00:11:12.970 --> 00:11:17.140
beginning with William
Congreve's preface in 1692

00:11:17.140 --> 00:11:20.990
to Incognita in which he
declares that romance elevates

00:11:20.990 --> 00:11:25.660
and surprises the reader
into a giddy delight.

00:11:25.660 --> 00:11:28.110
Scholars often oppose
the romance

00:11:28.110 --> 00:11:31.310
to the novel stipulating
the former is infatuated

00:11:31.310 --> 00:11:35.240
with the extraordinary,
the latter with the real.

00:11:35.240 --> 00:11:38.400
So, this idea that romance
really is talking about things

00:11:38.400 --> 00:11:41.720
that could not possibly be,
it's fantasy, extraordinary,

00:11:41.720 --> 00:11:45.190
and the novel is grounded
I a notion of realism.

00:11:45.190 --> 00:11:48.580
Within this critical tradition,
romance pertains to things

00:11:48.580 --> 00:11:51.310
that are un-observable
that can never be observed.

00:11:51.310 --> 00:11:53.460
And, it's a classic description

00:11:53.460 --> 00:11:57.520
that refuses experimental
verification.

00:11:57.520 --> 00:12:00.530
So, that's a kind of
truism in the field.

00:12:00.530 --> 00:12:02.590
So, what I want to point
out is that none other

00:12:02.590 --> 00:12:07.540
than Robert Boyle is a founding
member of the Royal Society,

00:12:07.540 --> 00:12:11.250
a father of chemistry, and
an extraordinary scientist.

00:12:11.250 --> 00:12:14.130
None other than Robert Boyle
challenged the perception

00:12:14.130 --> 00:12:19.180
that romance exclusively obtains
to unverifiable experience.

00:12:19.180 --> 00:12:21.770
Among his many intellectual
pursuits,

00:12:21.770 --> 00:12:26.370
Boyle pondered the principles of
romance and natural philosophy,

00:12:26.370 --> 00:12:29.090
the purportedly antithetical
realms

00:12:29.090 --> 00:12:31.890
of the imaginative
and the observable.

00:12:31.890 --> 00:12:34.190
He offered a text,
it's now lost,

00:12:34.190 --> 00:12:37.170
but it called Apology
for Romances.

00:12:37.170 --> 00:12:39.500
He also published
his own romance

00:12:39.500 --> 00:12:42.190
which he panned as a young man.

00:12:42.190 --> 00:12:46.400
In a text that he published
in 1671, the Excellency

00:12:46.400 --> 00:12:49.810
of Theology Compared
with Natural Philosophy,

00:12:49.810 --> 00:12:53.070
Boyle makes a comparison
similar to the one

00:12:53.070 --> 00:12:55.600
that Fontenelle makes
in preface.

00:12:56.690 --> 00:12:59.200
The experience of
nature and romances,

00:12:59.200 --> 00:13:02.620
Boyle argues, is analogical.

00:13:02.620 --> 00:13:06.800
In the Book of Nature, as
in a well contrived romance,

00:13:06.800 --> 00:13:10.380
the parts have such a connection
in relation to one another

00:13:10.380 --> 00:13:12.850
and the things we would
discover are darkly

00:13:12.850 --> 00:13:16.730
or incompletely knowable
by those that perceive them

00:13:16.730 --> 00:13:19.460
that the mind is never
satisfied till it comes

00:13:19.460 --> 00:13:21.830
to the end of the book.

00:13:21.830 --> 00:13:26.220
In other words, the intricacy
of the natural world correlates

00:13:26.220 --> 00:13:28.470
to that of the romance world.

00:13:28.470 --> 00:13:32.380
The connection supposes, though
it does not fully depict,

00:13:32.380 --> 00:13:35.390
a philosopher and a
reader who share the skill

00:13:35.390 --> 00:13:38.020
of careful observation.

00:13:38.020 --> 00:13:42.580
Romance may induce an absorptive
reader, but it also primes

00:13:42.580 --> 00:13:45.350
that reader to perceive
the meaningful data

00:13:45.350 --> 00:13:48.780
of the natural world.

00:13:48.780 --> 00:13:52.130
Now, Fontenelle's choice
of La Princess de Cleves,

00:13:52.130 --> 00:13:56.950
as an intellectual model,
also establishes an early link

00:13:56.950 --> 00:13:58.250
to the seduction plot.

00:13:58.250 --> 00:14:01.930
La Princess de Cleves
is a seduction story

00:14:01.930 --> 00:14:04.930
that follows the effective
tangle of the married woman

00:14:04.930 --> 00:14:08.020
and a nobleman, the
narrative trajectory

00:14:08.020 --> 00:14:09.890
and the educational imperative

00:14:09.890 --> 00:14:14.120
in Fontenelle's text require
a conversion to Copernican

00:14:14.120 --> 00:14:16.850
and Cartesian principles.

00:14:16.850 --> 00:14:22.770
And, Fontenelle understands this
conversion as a seduction story.

00:14:22.770 --> 00:14:25.610
In other words, seduction
allows Fontenelle

00:14:25.610 --> 00:14:30.080
to take a literary plot and uses
it to narrate how one learns

00:14:30.080 --> 00:14:32.890
and comes to believe
natural philosophy.

00:14:32.890 --> 00:14:38.390
In the first dialogue,
the Martianess

00:14:38.390 --> 00:14:42.180
and the Philosopher enjoy a
walk in the garden after supper

00:14:42.180 --> 00:14:45.540
as they discuss the
beauty of the night sky.

00:14:45.540 --> 00:14:50.610
It is a time, they determine,
most amenable to lovers.

00:14:50.610 --> 00:14:53.680
The philosopher's
description is luxurious.

00:14:53.680 --> 00:14:57.540
We have the moon
shining through the trees

00:14:57.540 --> 00:15:01.410
that checkers the paths beneath
a most resplendent bite upon

00:15:01.410 --> 00:15:02.810
the green.

00:15:02.810 --> 00:15:07.350
The stars looked all like pure
polished gold whose luster was

00:15:07.350 --> 00:15:09.960
extremely heightened by
the deep assured field

00:15:09.960 --> 00:15:12.170
on which they were placed.

00:15:12.170 --> 00:15:15.310
When the philosopher praises
the beauty of daytime,

00:15:15.310 --> 00:15:19.270
the Martianess turns to
metaphor, day and night as fair

00:15:19.270 --> 00:15:22.550
and dark ladies, the
latter of whom are superior.

00:15:22.550 --> 00:15:26.740
She also insists that that the
Philosopher agree with her.

00:15:26.740 --> 00:15:30.220
Nighttime and dark haired
women produce soft effects

00:15:30.220 --> 00:15:32.060
that lead to romance.

00:15:32.060 --> 00:15:36.270
She says, as you see,
how comes it that lovers

00:15:36.270 --> 00:15:39.230
who are the best judges of
what is pleasing and touching

00:15:39.230 --> 00:15:41.350
to always address
themselves to the night

00:15:41.350 --> 00:15:44.140
in all their songs and elegies?

00:15:44.140 --> 00:15:46.760
Both the Martianess and the
Philosopher become averted

00:15:46.760 --> 00:15:49.770
in how daylight obscures
the stars.

00:15:49.770 --> 00:15:54.220
The star filled night sky
facilitates or roving fancies

00:15:54.220 --> 00:15:57.950
about the universe in a
way that daylight cannot.

00:15:57.950 --> 00:16:02.360
Enlightenment occurs in
the absence of the sun.

00:16:02.360 --> 00:16:05.100
The Martianess says she has
always felt those effects

00:16:05.100 --> 00:16:09.930
of night you tell me, I love the
stars and could be hardly angry

00:16:09.930 --> 00:16:12.900
with the sun for taking
them from my sight.

00:16:12.900 --> 00:16:16.070
Her sentiment prompts the
Philosopher to explain,

00:16:16.070 --> 00:16:18.990
I cannot forgive the sun's
taking from me the sight

00:16:18.990 --> 00:16:22.360
of all those worlds
that there are.

00:16:22.360 --> 00:16:26.150
With that, the Martianess's
curiosity is peak

00:16:26.150 --> 00:16:28.800
and also insatiable.

00:16:28.800 --> 00:16:32.020
Worlds, she said, what worlds?

00:16:32.020 --> 00:16:35.980
This is the question the
forms the provocation

00:16:35.980 --> 00:16:38.630
for the ensuing scientific
dialogue.

00:16:38.630 --> 00:16:42.090
The Philosopher immediately
sees the swerve from Romance

00:16:42.090 --> 00:16:44.550
to cosmology as a loss

00:16:44.550 --> 00:16:46.650
of an opportunity
for sexual seduction.

00:16:46.650 --> 00:16:50.010
And, he's afraid he'll
be faulted for this.

00:16:50.010 --> 00:16:54.800
He says, oh Madam, I shall
never endure to be reproached

00:16:54.800 --> 00:16:57.810
with that neglect of
my own happiness, that,

00:16:57.810 --> 00:17:01.390
in a grove at ten o'clock
at night, I talk of nothing

00:17:01.390 --> 00:17:04.380
but philosophy to the
greatest beauty in the world.

00:17:04.380 --> 00:17:08.990
No Madam, search for
philosophy somewhere else.

00:17:08.990 --> 00:17:12.570
He resists, she insists,
and the moment

00:17:12.570 --> 00:17:14.960
for seduction seems to be lost.

00:17:14.960 --> 00:17:18.680
Astronomy displaces eroticism.

00:17:18.680 --> 00:17:22.250
However, rather than abandon
the seductive framework

00:17:22.250 --> 00:17:26.510
that he evokes here, Fontenelle,
instead, re-calibrates it.

00:17:26.510 --> 00:17:30.300
The garden bathed in moonlight
first allows the Philosopher

00:17:30.300 --> 00:17:34.240
to articular his own
double seduction.

00:17:34.240 --> 00:17:38.430
He is seduced by the prospect of
other worlds and he is seduced

00:17:38.430 --> 00:17:42.110
by the intellectual
desires of the Martianess.

00:17:42.110 --> 00:17:45.180
The text explicitly
characterizes the Philosopher

00:17:45.180 --> 00:17:48.870
as succumbing to the
Martianess's seduction.

00:17:48.870 --> 00:17:53.360
He says, but twas in vain
to put here off by excuses.

00:17:53.360 --> 00:17:58.110
From a novelty she was already
but too much pre-possesed with.

00:17:58.110 --> 00:18:03.090
He says there was a necessity of
yielding and all I could do was

00:18:03.090 --> 00:18:08.700
to prevail with her to be secret
for the saving of my honor.

00:18:08.700 --> 00:18:11.980
Cosmology and the
Martianess are both alluring.

00:18:11.980 --> 00:18:14.680
They both seduce
the Philosopher.

00:18:14.680 --> 00:18:19.570
He capitulates the desires
for the language of surrender.

00:18:19.570 --> 00:18:23.880
I found myself engaged
past retreat.

00:18:23.880 --> 00:18:28.640
Such enjoinder, such resignation
could easily be transported

00:18:28.640 --> 00:18:30.550
from the voice of
the desperate heroine

00:18:30.550 --> 00:18:31.850
in a seduction narrative.

00:18:31.850 --> 00:18:38.240
Now, even if one is tempted
to dismiss this opening scene,

00:18:38.240 --> 00:18:41.750
which really precipitates
the entire dialogue,

00:18:41.750 --> 00:18:43.680
as merely a contrivance.

00:18:43.680 --> 00:18:46.780
Fontenelle returns
to the same process

00:18:46.780 --> 00:18:49.520
of seduction on the fifth night.

00:18:49.520 --> 00:18:50.990
At this point, the Martianess

00:18:50.990 --> 00:18:53.440
and the Philosopher
are discussing those

00:18:53.440 --> 00:18:55.620
Cartesian Vortices.

00:18:55.620 --> 00:18:59.370
The topic supplies fanciable
and humorous [inaudible].

00:18:59.370 --> 00:19:01.780
The Martianess says,
for example,

00:19:01.780 --> 00:19:05.580
let my brains turn round
if they will as if you're

00:19:05.580 --> 00:19:09.610
on a spinning world and
everything about us is spinning.

00:19:09.610 --> 00:19:12.340
Amidst this conversation,
the Philosopher confess

00:19:12.340 --> 00:19:15.380
that his one distemper is love.

00:19:15.380 --> 00:19:19.540
They, wherein the turbilones
[assumed spelling] are not

00:19:19.540 --> 00:19:20.840
concerned at all.

00:19:20.840 --> 00:19:25.210
An infinite multitude of other
worlds may render little this

00:19:25.210 --> 00:19:29.520
in your esteem, but they do not
spoil fine eyes, a pretty mouth,

00:19:29.520 --> 00:19:32.810
or make the charms
of whit ever less.

00:19:32.810 --> 00:19:36.270
These will still have their
true values, still bear a price

00:19:36.270 --> 00:19:39.320
in spite of all the
worlds and universe.

00:19:39.320 --> 00:19:40.820
So, what he's saying is that,

00:19:40.820 --> 00:19:43.960
in spite of all the
astronomical discoveries

00:19:43.960 --> 00:19:48.240
and cosmological discoveries
he might encounter and all

00:19:48.240 --> 00:19:52.430
of these discoveries that might
changes one's view of the world,

00:19:52.430 --> 00:19:56.420
none of this will challenge
is ideas about love.

00:19:56.420 --> 00:19:59.980
The Martianes laughs and
states, love sames himself

00:19:59.980 --> 00:20:02.560
from all dangers and
there's no system

00:20:02.560 --> 00:20:04.380
or opinion that can hurt him.

00:20:04.380 --> 00:20:07.730
Now, the dialogue's
turn to love does more

00:20:07.730 --> 00:20:09.030
than offer the Philosopher

00:20:09.030 --> 00:20:11.230
and the Martianess an
excuse for reporte.

00:20:11.230 --> 00:20:14.950
And, they are endlessly kind
of charming and flirting

00:20:14.950 --> 00:20:17.030
with each other in this way.

00:20:17.030 --> 00:20:20.620
Falling in love is the
process of giving oneself

00:20:20.620 --> 00:20:23.960
over to the possibility
of seduction.

00:20:23.960 --> 00:20:25.960
And this acts as a model

00:20:25.960 --> 00:20:29.150
of [inaudible] acquisition
within the text.

00:20:29.150 --> 00:20:33.590
Scientific education, within
Fontenelle's dialogue,

00:20:33.590 --> 00:20:38.310
requires that a learner,
fundamentally, be seduced.

00:20:40.440 --> 00:20:42.580
Since we are always in the humor

00:20:42.580 --> 00:20:44.580
of mixing some little
gallantries

00:20:44.580 --> 00:20:47.920
with the most serious
discourses, give me lead

00:20:47.920 --> 00:20:51.170
to tell you that
mathematical reasoning is,

00:20:51.170 --> 00:20:54.760
in some things, near
a kin to love.

00:20:54.760 --> 00:20:58.350
You cannot allow the smallest
favor to a lover, but,

00:20:58.350 --> 00:21:01.610
he will soon persuade
you to yield another,

00:21:01.610 --> 00:21:03.880
and after that, a little more.

00:21:03.880 --> 00:21:06.800
And, in the end,
prevails entirely.

00:21:06.800 --> 00:21:10.420
So, if you grab the least
principles to a mathematician,

00:21:10.420 --> 00:21:13.140
he will instantly draw
consequences from it,

00:21:13.140 --> 00:21:18.140
which you must yield also, and
from that another, and a third,

00:21:18.140 --> 00:21:21.580
and maugre all your
resistance in a short time.

00:21:21.580 --> 00:21:25.550
He will lead you so far
that you cannot retreat.

00:21:25.550 --> 00:21:27.720
And, this is one of the
most remarkable lines.

00:21:27.720 --> 00:21:31.370
These two sorts of men, the
lover and the philosopher,

00:21:31.370 --> 00:21:34.700
always take more
than is given them.

00:21:34.700 --> 00:21:38.640
Persuasion here is seduction.

00:21:38.640 --> 00:21:41.370
Fontenelle's Philosopher
recounts the step

00:21:41.370 --> 00:21:46.010
by step process wherein one
figure inculcates another

00:21:46.010 --> 00:21:51.280
into a new world view, whether
it concerns amatory relations

00:21:51.280 --> 00:21:53.330
or cosmology.

00:21:53.330 --> 00:21:56.790
The process of seduction
is inherently social,

00:21:56.790 --> 00:22:00.830
whether it is embodied between
two lovers or whether it is

00:22:00.830 --> 00:22:04.430
in virtual between a
learned text and a reader.

00:22:04.430 --> 00:22:07.560
And, it relies upon
the lure of reading

00:22:07.560 --> 00:22:10.960
as one finds oneself swept
up on a rushing current

00:22:10.960 --> 00:22:14.420
of proposition after
proposition.

00:22:14.420 --> 00:22:17.620
The leading cosmology
results from a series

00:22:17.620 --> 00:22:21.380
of actions enacted by another.

00:22:21.380 --> 00:22:25.250
Those actions transport
an individual from one set

00:22:25.250 --> 00:22:27.910
of beliefs to another, a dynamic

00:22:27.910 --> 00:22:31.960
that mimics the narrative
structure of seduction stories.

00:22:31.960 --> 00:22:35.030
The conclusion whether
an intellectual

00:22:35.030 --> 00:22:38.680
or amatory terms is submission.

00:22:38.680 --> 00:22:42.570
While the Philosopher, in the
opening pages, positions himself

00:22:42.570 --> 00:22:45.170
as succumbing to the
Martianess's ardent desire

00:22:45.170 --> 00:22:49.080
to know about cosmology, he,
here, turns to the Martianess

00:22:49.080 --> 00:22:54.060
to tell her you are too
far engaged to retire

00:22:54.060 --> 00:22:58.590
and therefore you
must generously yield.

00:22:58.590 --> 00:23:02.610
Submission confirms
consent and agreement.

00:23:02.610 --> 00:23:07.550
She says, I yield and confess
you overcharge me with worlds

00:23:07.550 --> 00:23:09.300
and terbiens [assumed spelling].

00:23:09.300 --> 00:23:12.130
She announces her confession.

00:23:12.130 --> 00:23:18.230
I am extremely in love with
these ideas you give me.

00:23:18.230 --> 00:23:21.350
In Fontenelle's text,
we see the delineation

00:23:21.350 --> 00:23:25.000
of scientific education
that draws upon and in

00:23:25.000 --> 00:23:28.170
so doing revises
the torpid seduction

00:23:28.170 --> 00:23:32.040
so often associated
with sexual coercion.

00:23:32.040 --> 00:23:34.320
The setting of nighttime
being bathed

00:23:34.320 --> 00:23:37.650
in moonlight could be
seen and generally is seen

00:23:37.650 --> 00:23:40.990
as anticipating a
neurotic encounter.

00:23:40.990 --> 00:23:43.660
But, it is an equally
appropriate environment

00:23:43.660 --> 00:23:46.310
for a discussion of cosmology.

00:23:46.310 --> 00:23:50.310
Of course, sex and the cosmos
are never far from each other.

00:23:50.310 --> 00:23:52.750
The subject position
that Fontenelle imagines

00:23:52.750 --> 00:23:56.590
for his Martianess depends
upon careful observation

00:23:56.590 --> 00:23:57.920
and learning.

00:23:57.920 --> 00:24:01.120
And, it also depends upon
her willingness and ability

00:24:01.120 --> 00:24:03.240
to be seduced into
the Copernican

00:24:03.240 --> 00:24:04.940
and Cartesian imaginary.

00:24:04.940 --> 00:24:08.890
Now, I want to, the
last portion is

00:24:08.890 --> 00:24:12.340
to talk a little bit
briefly about Algarotti.

00:24:14.370 --> 00:24:18.180
Francesco Algarotti
published his text,

00:24:18.180 --> 00:24:20.930
and I don't have Italian,
but, it's translated

00:24:20.930 --> 00:24:24.750
by Elizabeth Carter as Sir Isaac
Newton's Philosophy Explained

00:24:24.750 --> 00:24:26.300
for the Use of the Ladies.

00:24:26.300 --> 00:24:29.870
He published it in 1737.

00:24:29.870 --> 00:24:34.150
The title pages means Naples is
a place of publication, though,

00:24:34.150 --> 00:24:38.560
it was printed in Milan under
somewhat covert circumstances.

00:24:38.560 --> 00:24:41.950
And I'd love to know more about
this but, it's a murky history.

00:24:41.950 --> 00:24:46.640
Newton for the Ladies went
through six Italian editions

00:24:46.640 --> 00:24:50.770
in the six years after
its original publication

00:24:50.770 --> 00:24:53.040
with ten more by 1812.

00:24:53.040 --> 00:24:55.160
And, it was also translated,
as you can imagine,

00:24:55.160 --> 00:24:59.180
quickly in the English,
French, Russian, Swedish,

00:24:59.180 --> 00:25:01.310
German, and Portuguese.

00:25:01.310 --> 00:25:04.620
So, it moved across
national linguistic borders

00:25:04.620 --> 00:25:07.950
and it moved across the century.

00:25:07.950 --> 00:25:12.810
So, Newton for the Ladies does
not denounce Copernicanism.

00:25:12.810 --> 00:25:16.480
And therefore, it, just as
Fontenelle's text was placed

00:25:16.480 --> 00:25:21.430
on the Catholic Church's
index of forbidden books.

00:25:21.430 --> 00:25:24.490
Also, like his predicessor,
Algarotti uses the genre

00:25:24.490 --> 00:25:26.200
of the scientific dialogue.

00:25:26.200 --> 00:25:29.080
Algarotti's appropriation

00:25:29.080 --> 00:25:32.460
of the seduction plot
demonstrates the persistence

00:25:32.460 --> 00:25:36.760
of this plot as a means to
enact scientific education.

00:25:36.760 --> 00:25:38.800
The science he teaches
is different.

00:25:38.800 --> 00:25:42.110
But Algarotti models
his dialogue explicitly

00:25:42.110 --> 00:25:43.570
on Fontenelle's.

00:25:43.570 --> 00:25:45.460
At the moment that
the Noble Woman,

00:25:45.460 --> 00:25:49.280
insists upon an education,
this time in Newton's theories

00:25:49.280 --> 00:25:53.610
of light and color, Algarotti
evokes his predecessor.

00:25:53.610 --> 00:25:56.960
In response to the Noble Woman,
the Philosopher begs she would

00:25:56.960 --> 00:25:59.430
at least had patience
till evening,

00:25:59.430 --> 00:26:02.330
telling her that the night had
always been the time consecrated

00:26:02.330 --> 00:26:04.410
to philosophical affairs,

00:26:04.410 --> 00:26:06.850
explaining that the
most polite philosopher

00:26:06.850 --> 00:26:11.230
in France had made use of it in
a circumstance resembling mine

00:26:11.230 --> 00:26:14.590
and made no scruple of
entertaining a fine lady

00:26:14.590 --> 00:26:19.220
with philosophical discourses,
and would at midnight.

00:26:19.220 --> 00:26:23.210
Yet, Algarotti's Noble
Woman is impatient.

00:26:23.210 --> 00:26:26.140
She spoke with this, she spoke
this with an era of authority

00:26:26.140 --> 00:26:29.290
that enforced her commands
in the most amiable manner

00:26:29.290 --> 00:26:33.370
and made it a pleasure to
obey, says the Philosopher.

00:26:33.370 --> 00:26:37.320
The Martianess's refusal here to
accede to the Philosopher desire

00:26:37.320 --> 00:26:40.760
to nighttime [inaudible]
reflects her agency

00:26:40.760 --> 00:26:45.420
and her greater rank of course
and also has the effect of,

00:26:45.420 --> 00:26:48.560
surprise, surprise, increasing
the Philosopher's desire

00:26:48.560 --> 00:26:52.050
to be seduced by her
intellectual philosophy.

00:26:52.050 --> 00:26:56.200
When the Philosopher fails to
seduce the Martianess sexually,

00:26:56.200 --> 00:26:57.810
he finds herself, instead,

00:26:57.810 --> 00:27:01.580
seduced by her epistemological
desires.

00:27:01.580 --> 00:27:05.860
Philosophers, argues the
Philosopher, are no different

00:27:05.860 --> 00:27:09.620
from mistresses, for, both
have the obligation, he says,

00:27:09.620 --> 00:27:12.100
to make good on their promises.

00:27:12.100 --> 00:27:15.910
A mistresses must accede to
enter into a sexual relation

00:27:15.910 --> 00:27:20.640
and a philosopher into
an intellectual one.

00:27:20.640 --> 00:27:23.130
But, the pathway of
seduction works both ways.

00:27:23.130 --> 00:27:25.930
If the Martianess seduces the
Philosopher with her desire

00:27:25.930 --> 00:27:29.600
to return, to learn,
the Newtonianism,

00:27:29.600 --> 00:27:33.730
presented by the Philosopher,
in turn, seduces her.

00:27:33.730 --> 00:27:38.530
As in Fontenelle,
mathematicians are like lovers.

00:27:38.530 --> 00:27:43.330
If what you grant them, at first
be ever so little, they know how

00:27:43.330 --> 00:27:45.540
to make so good an
advantage of it

00:27:45.540 --> 00:27:47.630
as to lead you insensibly
farther

00:27:47.630 --> 00:27:50.100
than you've ever imagined.

00:27:50.100 --> 00:27:54.110
Even though the Martianess
demurs, he says,

00:27:54.110 --> 00:27:57.750
I have as little skill
in the artifices of love

00:27:57.750 --> 00:28:00.490
as in the those of
philosophy and mathematics.

00:28:00.490 --> 00:28:03.720
She's enchanted by
and ultimately seduced

00:28:03.720 --> 00:28:06.840
by the principles
of Newtonianism.

00:28:06.840 --> 00:28:09.960
Her epistemological
craving returns throughout

00:28:09.960 --> 00:28:11.380
their dialogues.

00:28:11.380 --> 00:28:15.020
She felt, as you see,
the utmost impatience

00:28:15.020 --> 00:28:16.640
to be more learned than hugan.

00:28:16.640 --> 00:28:20.480
She was not for losing
a moment's time

00:28:20.480 --> 00:28:23.350
but would continued our
discourses upon vision the next

00:28:23.350 --> 00:28:26.650
morning as soon as
ever we were up.

00:28:26.650 --> 00:28:28.260
This was all the
optics she could get

00:28:28.260 --> 00:28:30.000
from me in the morning.

00:28:30.000 --> 00:28:32.550
Following an extensive
discussion concerning the

00:28:32.550 --> 00:28:36.400
refrangibility of light,
the Philosopher responds

00:28:36.400 --> 00:28:38.910
to the Martianess in terms
that points to the structure

00:28:38.910 --> 00:28:42.220
of desire and to the
plot of seduction.

00:28:42.220 --> 00:28:45.780
Tis in philosphy, as in
all other human affairs

00:28:45.780 --> 00:28:47.080
where the accomplishment

00:28:47.080 --> 00:28:50.350
of one desire often
gives birth to another.

00:28:50.350 --> 00:28:53.520
And, you have that same process
that you saw in Fontenelle.

00:28:53.520 --> 00:28:56.030
As soon as you learn a little
bit, you want to learn more

00:28:56.030 --> 00:28:58.460
and you want to learn more,
it's a structured desire.

00:28:58.460 --> 00:29:03.050
So, the female reader of
Algarotti's text is imagined

00:29:03.050 --> 00:29:06.950
as an eager recipient
ready to be swayed

00:29:06.950 --> 00:29:10.440
by the seductive allure
of Newtonian science.

00:29:10.440 --> 00:29:13.430
She is an effective being.

00:29:13.430 --> 00:29:15.290
And, the plot of
seduction is appropriate

00:29:15.290 --> 00:29:17.750
because it concerns affect,

00:29:17.750 --> 00:29:21.520
namely a subject's heart
rather than her mind.

00:29:21.520 --> 00:29:23.030
And, in this way, Algarotti

00:29:23.030 --> 00:29:24.880
and Fontenelle are a
little bit different.

00:29:24.880 --> 00:29:27.530
Algarotti writes, the marvelous

00:29:27.530 --> 00:29:31.050
of which the heart always
desires of being effected is

00:29:31.050 --> 00:29:36.260
so fond happily arises in
true philosophy of itself

00:29:36.260 --> 00:29:37.560
with out the help of machines.

00:29:37.560 --> 00:29:40.930
And then, he asks,
is there anything

00:29:40.930 --> 00:29:45.750
in which a writer should omit
any endeavors to move the heart.

00:29:45.750 --> 00:29:47.050
So, the role of affect

00:29:47.050 --> 00:29:50.610
and seduction introduces the
possibility that the conversion

00:29:50.610 --> 00:29:53.880
to Newtonianism may not succeed.

00:29:53.880 --> 00:29:57.170
Because, she perceives
rather than understands,

00:29:57.170 --> 00:30:01.430
she is effected by and
receives Newtonianism,

00:30:01.430 --> 00:30:04.410
the Martianess second
guesses herself.

00:30:04.410 --> 00:30:06.290
When they discuss
the refrangibility

00:30:06.290 --> 00:30:08.350
of light, she panics.

00:30:08.350 --> 00:30:12.230
She asks have I acted
wrong in suffering myself

00:30:12.230 --> 00:30:14.960
to be too easily convinced?

00:30:14.960 --> 00:30:20.070
The Philosopher assures her that
a lady cannot err in this point.

00:30:20.070 --> 00:30:24.640
Uncertainty does not derail
the conversion process.

00:30:24.640 --> 00:30:30.600
She says, let me intrigue you
to make me a complete Newtonian.

00:30:30.600 --> 00:30:35.060
I plainly see, by my conversion,
I so shall inquire the knowledge

00:30:35.060 --> 00:30:37.410
of truth without
losing that pleasure

00:30:37.410 --> 00:30:40.440
which I found in being deceived.

00:30:40.440 --> 00:30:43.310
And, the end of their six
dialogues accomplishes her

00:30:43.310 --> 00:30:45.310
desire for conversion.

00:30:45.310 --> 00:30:50.950
If the Martianess is seduced by
the ideas of Newtonianism, then,

00:30:50.950 --> 00:30:52.690
she provokes a philosopher

00:30:52.690 --> 00:30:56.560
by placing Newton himself
within such a plot.

00:30:57.860 --> 00:31:01.950
You seem to represent nature
as a coquette she says,

00:31:01.950 --> 00:31:04.720
and Sir Isaac Newton
as a jealous lover

00:31:04.720 --> 00:31:06.430
who never thinks
he has proof enough

00:31:06.430 --> 00:31:08.940
of the fidelity of his mistress.

00:31:08.940 --> 00:31:12.780
The Martianess's portrait of
Newton recalls a scientific

00:31:12.780 --> 00:31:14.080
and erotic legacy

00:31:14.080 --> 00:31:17.530
of masculinized intellectual
mastery commonly found

00:31:17.530 --> 00:31:19.890
in Bacon and his followers.

00:31:19.890 --> 00:31:23.810
The process of acquiring
natural philosophical knowledge

00:31:23.810 --> 00:31:25.970
that then can be distributed

00:31:25.970 --> 00:31:30.770
to alkalies requires endless
experimentation and pursuit.

00:31:30.770 --> 00:31:35.800
A single experiment does
not satisfy a philosopher.

00:31:35.800 --> 00:31:39.890
The Philosopher answers this
was the only object of his love.

00:31:39.890 --> 00:31:43.450
He confirms the legitimacy
and compares them and suggests

00:31:43.450 --> 00:31:48.630
that Newton's rightful posture
was of a jealous love driven

00:31:48.630 --> 00:31:50.430
to distraction to find out any

00:31:50.430 --> 00:31:53.500
and all secrets of
the natural world.

00:31:53.500 --> 00:31:55.570
Newton, as a natural
philosopher,

00:31:55.570 --> 00:31:59.410
embodies the suspicion
of a controlling lover.

00:31:59.410 --> 00:32:04.730
However, Algarotti's Philosopher
presses for a key difference.

00:32:04.730 --> 00:32:08.090
So, Newton exhibits
philosophical jealousy.

00:32:08.090 --> 00:32:11.260
And this very vividly
binds the seduction revert

00:32:11.260 --> 00:32:13.610
to scientific discovery.

00:32:13.610 --> 00:32:15.480
Under writing the
process of seduction

00:32:15.480 --> 00:32:19.000
that the Philosopher here
and the Martianess undergo,

00:32:19.000 --> 00:32:21.570
is a super structure that
understands seduction

00:32:21.570 --> 00:32:24.600
as a relation of
power and control.

00:32:24.600 --> 00:32:28.040
Newton's knowledge acquisition
does not reside an ecstatic

00:32:28.040 --> 00:32:32.250
realm but forcibly
encounters nature, its subject,

00:32:32.250 --> 00:32:35.800
and bends nature to its
practitioner's will.

00:32:35.800 --> 00:32:38.240
The Philosopher qualifies
the admission

00:32:38.240 --> 00:32:42.310
that Newton too has the
desires of a seducer.

00:32:42.310 --> 00:32:44.020
At the text's conclusion,

00:32:44.020 --> 00:32:46.360
he distinguishes the
Martianess's passions

00:32:46.360 --> 00:32:48.910
from Newton's moderation.

00:32:48.910 --> 00:32:52.810
So, the Philosopher says, the
moderation of our philosophers

00:32:52.810 --> 00:32:55.140
in never affirming
anything to be true

00:32:55.140 --> 00:32:57.850
which was not demonstrated
by observation,

00:32:57.850 --> 00:33:02.600
may serve for an example
for most rash asserters.

00:33:02.600 --> 00:33:06.080
In spite of the Martianess's
enthusiastic response,

00:33:06.080 --> 00:33:08.790
the findings of Newton,
insists the Philosopher,

00:33:08.790 --> 00:33:11.100
are sober and reasoned.

00:33:11.100 --> 00:33:14.990
He says they are not assertions
but they are discoveries.

00:33:14.990 --> 00:33:17.950
Now, Algarotti's text we've
witnessed the multi-valient

00:33:17.950 --> 00:33:21.870
nature of the seduction paradigm
in ways that accord with

00:33:21.870 --> 00:33:25.110
and differ from the
precedent of Fontenelle.

00:33:25.110 --> 00:33:28.470
In Fontenelle, the Philosopher
reports the Martianess seduces

00:33:28.470 --> 00:33:31.250
him and the Martianess
admits that she is seduced

00:33:31.250 --> 00:33:34.450
by her scientific education.

00:33:34.450 --> 00:33:37.030
These are moments of learning.

00:33:37.030 --> 00:33:40.230
But, Algarotti privileges a
woman's power of perception

00:33:40.230 --> 00:33:43.190
over her understanding,
a form of cognition

00:33:43.190 --> 00:33:47.130
that excused Fontenelle's
celebration of the imagination

00:33:47.130 --> 00:33:50.710
and it presents feeling
as a mode of learning.

00:33:50.710 --> 00:33:54.360
Algarotti's texts highlights the
imperative for seduction built

00:33:54.360 --> 00:33:58.000
into the project of natural
philosophy as a practice.

00:33:58.000 --> 00:34:00.480
And, in this final
seduction, the producer

00:34:00.480 --> 00:34:04.300
of knowledge seduces a
vulnerable and feminized nature

00:34:04.300 --> 00:34:07.150
in the process of revealing
the gender an sexual politics

00:34:07.150 --> 00:34:09.630
of knowing and being known.

00:34:11.220 --> 00:34:14.530
To conclude, through their
evocation and adaptation

00:34:14.530 --> 00:34:18.110
of the seduction plot, these
scientific dialogues demonstrate

00:34:18.110 --> 00:34:20.980
that believing in science
is not merely a matter

00:34:20.980 --> 00:34:23.900
of rational understanding.

00:34:23.900 --> 00:34:26.960
The idea of virtual
witnessing that is written

00:34:26.960 --> 00:34:31.000
into the early scientific
project which is reading

00:34:31.000 --> 00:34:35.840
and believing experiments,
establishes textual mediation

00:34:35.840 --> 00:34:39.420
as a vital technology
of scientific inquiry.

00:34:39.420 --> 00:34:44.440
It ultimately depends up on
readers reading and imagining

00:34:44.440 --> 00:34:48.720
and thus corroborating the
accuracy of reported findings.

00:34:48.720 --> 00:34:52.090
But, the seduction plot
reveals another technology.

00:34:52.090 --> 00:34:54.830
Understood as a transformative
process,

00:34:54.830 --> 00:34:58.010
seduction plots move an
individual from one circumstance

00:34:58.010 --> 00:35:00.260
or one set of beliefs
to another.

00:35:00.260 --> 00:35:03.750
Seduction acts upon the
individuals who experience it.

00:35:03.750 --> 00:35:08.050
It pushes one beyond the limits
of rational disbelief or belief

00:35:08.050 --> 00:35:10.920
and it exacts submission.

00:35:10.920 --> 00:35:12.920
To use the seduction
plot as a model

00:35:12.920 --> 00:35:15.570
for scientific education spells

00:35:15.570 --> 00:35:20.020
out the conversion one must
undergo, the conversion

00:35:20.020 --> 00:35:22.810
to which one must be subjective

00:35:22.810 --> 00:35:25.100
to become a modern
enlightened subject.

